name: Isabion
usage: Mix 40ml/15L tank (12 tanks/acre). Apply 30-35 days after sowing (flowering). Can mix with Alika or Amistar. DO NOT mix with herbicides.

name: Alika
usage: Mix 8ml/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). Apply 20-25 days after sowing for sucking pests. Safe to mix with Isabion/Fungicides.

name: Amistar Top
usage: Mix 20ml/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). Apply 40 days after sowing for leaf spots. Can mix with Alika. Avoid mixing with heavy herbicides.

name: Quantis
usage: Mix 60ml/15L tank (16 tanks/acre). Apply 45 days after sowing for heat stress. Safe with most Insecticides. Safe with Alika.

name: Ampligo
usage: Mix 10ml/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). Apply 30 days after sowing for pod borer. Can mix with nutrients. DO NOT mix with herbicides.

name: Actara
usage: Mix 10g/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). Apply 15-20 days after sowing. Safe with Nutrients. Can mix with Icon 10CS.

name: Score
usage: Mix 15ml/15L tank (15 tanks/acre). Apply 50 days after sowing. Safe with Insecticides. Avoid mixing with strong Weedicides.

name: Icon 10CS
usage: Mix 20ml/15L tank for crops. Apply anytime for pests. Can mix with Actara. DO NOT mix with Growth Promoters (Isabion).

name: Ridomil Gold
usage: Mix 25g/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). Apply 15 days after sowing. Safe with most insecticides. DO NOT mix with herbicides.

name: Fusiflex
usage: Mix 50ml/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). Apply 15-20 days after sowing on wet soil. SPRAY ALONE. DO NOT mix with anything.

name: Cultar
usage: Mix 10ml/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). Used for growth regulation. Apply 40 days after sowing. Avoid mixing with herbicides.

name: Rifit
usage: Apply 500ml per acre within 3 days of sowing. Pre-emergence. DO NOT mix with any other chemical.

name: Simodis
usage: Mix 8ml/15L tank (10 tanks/acre). High-end protection for Thrips/Mites. Apply 25-30 days after sowing. Safe with Nutrients.

name: Demand
usage: Mix 20ml/15L tank. General pest control. Can mix with Fungicides. Avoid mixing with Isabion/Growth Promoters.

name: Ambition
usage: Plant growth activator with amino acids. Enhances flowering and reduces flower drop. Apply at 30-35 days.

name: Belt Expert
usage: Fast-acting control for Pod Borer and Thrips. Disrupts muscle and nervous system of pests.

name: Confidor
usage: Systemic control for sucking pests like Aphids and Jassids. Prevents Yellow Mosaic Virus spread.

name: Planofix
usage: Stops flower and immature pod shedding. Mix 1ml in 4.5L water for flowering stage spray.

name: Nativo
usage: Controls Powdery Mildew and Leaf Spot. Improves grain shine and weight significantly.

name: QuickBayt
usage: Fly bait for farm hygiene. Use as paint-on or scatter bait around storage areas. NOT for foliar spray.

name: Roundup
usage: Non-selective herbicide for spot spray on heavy weed patches or field bunds. Use with caution.

name: Sencor
usage: Pre-emergence herbicide. Spray on moist soil within 3 days of sowing to stop weed germination.

name: Solomon
usage: Quick knockdown effect on Whiteflies and Aphids. Innovative oil-based formula for better penetration.

name: Targa Super
usage: The specialist for killing grassy weeds in Blackgram. Safe to spray on the main crop.

name: Vayego
usage: Advanced systemic control for Pod Borers and Girdle Beetle. Long-lasting residual protection.

name: Argyle
usage: Dual action for Whitefly and Girdle Beetle. Helps manage resistance in pest populations.

name: Iris
usage: One-shot control for broad-leaf and grassy weeds. Apply 15-25 days after sowing.

name: Lancer Gold
usage: Premium control for sucking pests like Thrips and Aphids. Mix 400g per acre.

name: Macarena
usage: Bio-stimulant for better plant health and stress resistance. Boosts vegetative growth.

name: Saaf
usage: Best for seed treatment or early spray against Root Rot and Leaf Spot.

name: Shenzi
usage: Contains Chlorantraniliprole. Best-in-class protection against Pod Borers.

name: Coragen
usage: Industry leader for Pod Borer control. Provides 20+ days of crop protection.

name: Benevia
usage: Stops sucking pests and caterpillars. Apply early (20-25 days) for best yield start.

name: Marshal
usage: Stomach and contact poison for Aphids and Borers. Excellent knockdown effect.

name: Talstar
usage: Broad-spectrum spray for Whitefly, Bollworms, and Leaf Folders.

name: Zinatra
usage: High concentration Zinc (39.5%). Prevents yellowing of leaves and boosts shoot growth.

name: Bahaar
usage: Veg-based growth promoter. Improves chlorophyll and protein synthesis for more pods.

name: Panida
usage: Pre-emergence herbicide (Pendimethalin). Forms a layer to stop weed germination.

name: Ralligold
usage: Mycorrhizal bio-fertilizer. Dramatically improves root development and nutrient uptake.

name: Takumi
usage: High-tech granular insecticide for Maruca and Pod Borer. Stop feeding instantly.

name: Taqat
usage: Dual-action contact and systemic fungicide for Anthracnose and Mildew.
